RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BARBERA was asked to show speed leaving the break and dictated terms to the turn, set decent fractions to the quarter marker, was set down for the drive while holding the lead to the furlong pole, steadily drifted out while under left-handed urging in the stretch and carried out ENDLESS DREAM, kept to task to deep stretch and dug in in the final stages to prevail. ENDLESS DREAM was forwardly placed early on and stalked the pace to the turn, kept close attendance to BARBERA to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit of that foe to mid-stretch, advanced on BARBERA while being steadily carried out by that rival and was held at bay for the win in deep stretch, while holding safely for second. ROSE ROSE ROSE was unhurried in the early running, saved ground into the turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, closed well in the late stages, could not impact the top pair in deep stretch and was up in time to secure third. SWEET MILLIE lunged at the start and was off a step slowly, chased the decent early pace, gained ground while four wide on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, lacked the needed late response and was outfinished for third. WHATWASTHENISNOW chased the pace from the inside, ran evenly to the furlong grounds and gave way in the final stages. PRNCSS OF DEL MAR chased the decent early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, could not sustain that bid in the stretch drive and weakened. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT BARBERA STEADILY DRIFTED OUT INSIDE OF THE FURLONG MARKER AND CAUSED ENDLESS DREAM TO BE CARRIED OUT IN THE STRETCH. THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THIS ACTION BY BARBERA COST ENDLESS DREAM THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING, AND BARBERA WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AND PLACED SECOND.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEDAL ICE tracked WESTERN SIERRA to the turn under a firm hold, bid for the lead leaving the quarter pole, veered out under left handed urging in mid-stretch but was able to run down the stubborn pacesetter inside the furlong grounds. NICKEL NICKEL NINE broke out and bothered ANOTHER STRIKE after the break, chased the two leaders from well back while to the outside of EASTER TRIBUTE, moved in tandem with that one through the turn, swung three wide into the stretch, closed with a rush in the late stages and just missed for the win, while securing second. WESTERN SIERRA broke sharply then veered in front of ANOTHER STRIKE, was able to seize the early advantage then maintained a clear lead to the stretch, ran on well when roused down the lane, veered out late and just failed to last. EASTER TRIBUTE got away a bit slowly, saved ground through the turn, came under a ride approaching the five-sixteenths pole but could not summon the needed response. ANOTHER STRIKE broke in a bit at the start then over-reacted when the rider tried to straighten out, then had to steady when WESTERN SIERRA veered into the path, fought the rider down the backstretch then made a four wide bid on the turn to regain contact with the field, was gaining in the stretch drive but could not muster the needed late response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLONEL VARGO broke well then got good position on the inside of a three horse speed duel early, shook off the challengers on the turn, responded when roused at the top of the stretch and finished strong under intermittent urging to prevail. PERFORMATIVE veered in sharply at the break, bumped and impeded LIVERMORE HEAT then overcorrected in the opposite direction spotting the field a head start, was then unhurried near the rear of the field down the backstretch and into the turn, made a big sweeping move four to five wide with three furlongs to run, tipped six wide into the stretch then continued to rally, raced a bit erratically late and came up short. LIVERMORE HEAT bumped and impeded by PERFORMATIVE at the start, lagged far behind the field down the backstretch, was still out of touch on the turn then started a huge rally from the five-sixteenths pole that carried seven wide into the stretch, shifted inside mid-stretch to dodge an erratic PERFORMATIVE and gained third. WEE BEASTIE tracked early while saving ground, moved into contention on the turn, got a clear run into the stretch and ran on well down the lane but needed a bit more. UPDRAFT broke out at the start then had trouble getting straightened out, hustled to keep contact with the field, was under pressure and ran one-paced from start to finish. PLENTY COUPS broke alertly and was in the outside of a three horse speed duel early, bid three wide at the top of the stretch then failed to change leads and tired. MY DAD IS THIRSTY vied for the early lead between horses, was still in contention at the top of the stretch then weakened down the lane. SMOKIN BLAZE chased the early pace, lost position while three wide on the turn, was outrun in the drive and gave way.
